President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Iowa due to severe storms, flooding, and tornadoes that occurred starting from June 1, 2010. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in several counties. Additionally, funding will be provided for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Thomas A. Hall has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and deemed necessary based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.